## ❗ Problem Being Solved

Store managers manually analyse sales reports to identify trends.

* Takes **1–2 hours per week per store**
* Results vary depending on manager experience
* Slows down inventory decision-making

At scale (50+ stores), this creates **significant time cost and inconsistent planning decisions**.

---

## ⚡ Automation Potential

**Level: High**

| Dimension               | Assessment                                    |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Repetitiveness          | High — same analysis done weekly              |
| Data availability       | High — structured sales data always available |
| Human judgment needed   | Medium — insights need validation             |
| Integration possibility | High — outputs feed into forecasting tools    |
| Estimated time saving   | ~80% reduction in analysis time               |

**Human-in-the-loop role:**
Managers review insights before acting on inventory decisions.

